==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Zend-Avesta
<hw>Zend`-A*ves"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Properly,
the <ets>Avesta</ets>, or sacred text, and its <ets>zend</ets>, or
interpretation, in a more modern and intelligible language. <au>W. D.
Whitney.</au>]</ety> <def>The sacred writings of the ancient Persian
religion, attributed to Zoroaster, but chiefly of a later
date.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zendik</ent>⟦br⟧
